metadata.name: Tesseract #187
metadata.description:
'Tesseract' is a generative collection drawing on the concept of the cube from oneirology, the interpretation of dreams. In many mythologies and fields of study, the square is considered a 'perfect shape', thus with its abstraction into three isometric dimensions, the cube is seen by some as a representation of the various aspects of the human condition.

In 'Tesseract', the ribbons flowing between the cubes represent the shared experiences that connect us all. No matter how different our lives might be, we all go through the same joys, sorrows, trials, tribulations and experience attachments of varying degrees. 

It is these experiences that bind us together and make us who we are. With these concepts in mind, viewers are invited to interpret each composition as it relates to them and their unique story, from the perspective of that which has been and that which is yet to be experienced.

Press 'S' to save a high resolution PNG at 2400 x 3396 px.

metadata.name: Artificial Flower 2 (2022), walkers series #7
metadata.description:
The first version was made at 2016 year. That time I was experiment with random walkers. The idea behind this sketch is the same with some my other artworks: create visual complex result with the basic rules that sometimes has references to the classic generative art technics by repeating a lot of iterations and mixing that classic technics with new possibilities that p5js brings – currently for that sketch is "random walker" technics and p5js color mixing and change alpha channel.

The first name of this sketch was "Painter walk" but I'm think that it's more looks like a flower, Artificial Flower.

Randomisation based on hash:
1. Color1 and Color2, that randomly selected from the list of 10 colors. If Color1 and Color2 can't be the same color, but sometimes it can be the darker or lighter version of the same color may create 3D effect (alpha also make such effect).
2. Amount of walkers (lines)
3. Each walker has uniq size, lifespan and walk path
4. I hope that I didn't forgot to mention something that also use fxhash randomisation.

The v1 can be found at https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/4439

I hope you will like it. Soon I will publish more new sketches and than adapt and publish my old sketches that was made in period from 2012 to 2019 year. Some of artworks from my profile are new. This one is remake of my old sketch that was made in 2016.

Thanks.

metadata.name: Segments #382
metadata.description:
A continuous flowing motion of segmented cubes.

There is 5 routes for variations which is chosen by the 'Animation Type' variable. Each route then has it's own way to produce variety based on the random values injected into each.

Routes available (each is a type of noise used to change the animation of the cubes):
1. Waveform
2. Cellular
3. Voronoise
4. Polka Dots
5. Layers

Each route then has between 5 to 11 variables that will change the outcome of the overall look.

metadata.name: Sunset in Paradise #24
metadata.description:
Hundreds of Walkers descend the screen drawing a sky, sea and the sun reflection; creating a twilight scene of a sunset or possibly a sunrise depending on which coast your paradise can be found. 
Features - 32 Palettes 
5 Possible background colors per palette
3 different complexities of sky:
	-Refined - 3 colors (25% chance)
	-Complex - 5 colors (25% chance)
	-Normal - 4 colors (50% chance)
2 possible border colors: 
	Matching the sun color (40% chance) 
	Matching the sea color (60% chance)
2 different stroke thickness: 
	Fine (25% chance) 
	Medium-point (75% chance) 
Different amounts of Walkers for Sky, Sea and reflection.

Made by @p1x3lboy in p5.js
June 2022

metadata.name: Zephyr #71
metadata.description:
The name Zephyr traces back to Zephyrus, the Greek god of the west wind, and refers to any light breeze. The flowing particles get pushed around by a zephyr, creating interesting and organic patterns.

Live Mode Controls:

- Default is 2000x2000 pixel canvas. Press “1” for 1000x1000px canvas, “3” for 3000x3000px, “4” for 4000x4000px
- Press 'p' to save a png of the canvas.

Created using p5.js
